        <div class="sd-time">Surgery</div>
        <div class="sd-desc"><strong>The procedure takes 30&ndash;60 minutes</strong> for most hernias (longer for large, complex, or recurrent repairs). Under general anesthesia, Dr. Kakarla makes 3 small incisions on the side of the abdomen. The hernia contents are reduced back into the abdomen, the defect edges are sutured closed, and mesh is placed to reinforce the repair. A <strong>TAP block</strong> (numbing injection in the abdominal wall) is performed during surgery for post-operative pain control.</div>
